getInheritedInput
description:
Return state that comes from the container and is passed down to the child. For instance, time range and
filters are common inherited input state. Note that any state stored in `this.input.panels[embeddableId].explicitInput`
will override inherited input.

children.label: reload
description:
Reload will be called when there is a request to refresh the data or view, even if the
input data did not change.

In case if input data did change and reload is requested input$ and output$ would still emit before `reload` is called

The order would be as follows:
input$
output$
reload()
----
updated$

children.label: getUpdated$
description:
Merges input$ and output$ streams and debounces emit till next macro-task.
Could be useful to batch reactions to input$ and output$ updates that happen separately but synchronously.
In case corresponding state change triggered `reload` this stream is guarantied to emit later,
which allows to skip any state handling in case `reload` already handled it.

interfaces.label: Adapters
description: The interface that the adapters used to open an inspector have to fullfill.

interfaces.label: EmbeddableEditorState
description: A state package that contains information an editor will need to create or edit an embeddable then redirect back.

interfaces.label: EmbeddableFactory
description: EmbeddableFactories create and initialize an embeddable instance

children.label: isEditable
description:
Returns whether the current user should be allowed to edit this type of
embeddable. Most of the time this should be based off the capabilities service, hence it's async.

children.label: isContainerType
description:
True if is this factory create embeddables that are Containers. Used in the add panel to
conditionally show whether these can be added to another container. It's just not
supported right now, but once nested containers are officially supported we can probably get
rid of this interface.

children.label: getDisplayName
description:
Returns a display name for this type of embeddable. Used in "Create new... " options
in the add panel for containers.

children.label: canCreateNew
description:
If false, this type of embeddable can't be created with the "createNew" functionality. Instead,
use createFromSavedObject, where an existing saved object must first exist.

children.label: getDefaultInput
description:
Can be used to get any default input, to be passed in to during the creation process. Default
input will not be stored in a parent container, so any inherited input from a container will trump
default input parameters.

children.label: getExplicitInput
description:
Can be used to request explicit input from the user, to be passed in to `EmbeddableFactory:create`.
Explicit input is stored on the parent container for this embeddable. It overrides any inherited
input passed down from the parent container.

children.label: createFromSavedObject
description: Creates a new embeddable instance based off the saved object id.

children.label: input
description:
- some input may come from a parent, or user, if it's not stored with the saved object. For example, the time
range of the parent container.

children.label: create
description:
Resolves to undefined if a new Embeddable cannot be directly created and the user will instead be redirected
elsewhere.

This will likely change in future iterations when we improve in place editing capabilities.

interfaces.label: EmbeddablePackageState
description: A state package that contains all fields necessary to create or update an embeddable by reference or by value in a container.

children.label: untilEmbeddableLoaded
description: Call if you want to wait until an embeddable with that id has finished loading.

children.label: getInputForChild
description:
Returns the input for the given child. Uses a combination of explicit input
for the child stored on the parent and derived/inherited input taken from the
container itself.

children.label: updateInputForChild
description:
Changes the input for a given child. Note, this will override any inherited state taken from
the container itself.

children.label: getChild
description: Returns the child embeddable with the given id.

children.label: removeEmbeddable
description: Removes the embeddable with the given id.

children.label: addNewEmbeddable
description:
Adds a new embeddable to the container. `explicitInput` may partially specify the required embeddable input,
but the remainder must come from inherited container state.

children.label: isContainer
description:
Is this embeddable an instance of a Container class, can it contain
nested embeddables?

children.label: parent
description:
If this embeddable is nested inside a container, this will contain
a reference to its parent.

children.label: type
description:
The type of embeddable, this is what will be used to take a serialized
embeddable and find the correct factory for which to create an instance of it.

children.label: id
description:
A unique identifier for this embeddable. Mainly only used by containers to map their
Panel States to a child embeddable instance.

children.label: runtimeId
description:
Unique ID an embeddable is assigned each time it is initialized. This ID
is different for different instances of the same embeddable. For example,
if the same dashboard is rendered twice on the screen, all embeddable
instances will have a unique `runtimeId`.

children.label: enhancements
description: Extra abilities added to Embeddable by `*_enhanced` plugins.

children.label: fatalError
description: If this embeddable has encountered a fatal error, that error will be stored here

children.label: getIsContainer
description:
A functional representation of the isContainer variable, but helpful for typescript to
know the shape if this returns true

children.label: getInput
description:
Get the input used to instantiate this embeddable. The input is a serialized representation of
this embeddable instance and can be used to clone or re-instantiate it. Input state:

- Can be updated externally
- Can change multiple times for a single embeddable instance.

Examples: title, pie slice colors, custom search columns and sort order.

children.label: getOutput
description:
Output state is:

- State that should not change once the embeddable is instantiated, or
- State that is derived from the input state, or
- State that only the embeddable instance itself knows about, or the factory.

Examples: editUrl, title taken from a saved object, if your input state was first name and
  last name, your output state could be greeting.

children.label: updateInput
description: Updates input state with the given changes.

children.label: getInput$
description: Returns an observable which will be notified when input state changes.

children.label: getOutput$
description: Returns an observable which will be notified when output state changes.

children.label: getTitle
description: Returns the title of this embeddable.

children.label: getRoot
description:
Returns the top most parent embeddable, or itself if this embeddable
is not within a parent.

children.label: render
description: Renders the embeddable at the given node.

children.label: reload
description:
Reload the embeddable so output and rendering is up to date. Especially relevant
if the embeddable takes relative time as input (e.g. now to now-15)

children.label: getInspectorAdapters
description:
An embeddable can return inspector adapters if it wants the inspector to be
available via the context menu of that panel.
returnComment: Inspector adapters that will be used to open an inspector for.

children.label: destroy
description: Cleans up subscriptions, destroy nodes mounted from calls to render.

children.label: supportedTriggers
description: List of triggers that this embeddable will execute.

interfaces.label: ReferenceOrValueEmbeddable
description:
Any embeddable that implements this interface will be able to use input that is
either by reference (backed by a saved object) OR by value, (provided
by the container).

children.label: inputIsRefType
description: determines whether the input is by value or by reference.

children.label: getInputAsValueType
description: Gets the embeddable's current input as its Value type

children.label: getInputAsRefType
description: Gets the embeddable's current input as its Reference type

misc.label: ATTRIBUTE_SERVICE_KEY
description:
The attribute service is a shared, generic service that embeddables can use to provide the functionality
required to fulfill the requirements of the ReferenceOrValueEmbeddable interface. The attribute_service
can also be used as a higher level wrapper to transform an embeddable input shape that references a saved object
into an embeddable input shape that contains that saved object's attributes by value.

This type is a publicly exposed props of {@link EmbeddableRenderer}
Union is used to validate that or factory or embeddable is passed in, but it can't be both simultaneously
In case when embeddable is passed in, input is optional, because there is already an input inside of embeddable object
In case when factory is used, then input is required, because it will be used as initial input to create an embeddable object
